            "creation_date": 1450666133,
            "body": "<p>The <code>Unsupported major.minor version 52.0<\/code> error says that you have a Java 8 class file but a Java &lt;= 7 JRE. So you haven't succeeded in installing Java 8 for Tomcat at all. You may need to adjust something in the Tomcat configuration to make it use Java 8.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 34388282,
            "question_id": 34388165,
            "last_edit_date": 1467274568
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/uNBaT.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 131902,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 332248,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/332248/jens",
                "reputation": 6403,
                "display_name": "Jens",
                "accept_rate": 62
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 5,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1476458090,
            "creation_date": 1476458090,
            "body": "<p>If you happen to run Tomcat as a service on Windows you might need to change the JRE that tomcat uses by issuing: <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>tomcat7w.exe //ES/&lt;your_service_name&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Which should lead you to this dialog:<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/g28OE.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/g28OE.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>Make sure \"use default\" is ticked or the right \"Java virtual Machine\" is used.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 40046568,
            "question_id": 34388165
        }
